Thrifty-X
=========

This project is a derivative work of Thrifty, originally developed by
Schalk Willem Krüger at North-West University (South Africa).

Original project: https://github.com/swkrueger/Thrifty
Dissertation:     https://hdl.handle.net/10394/25449

Reference:
  Krüger, S.W. (2016). An inexpensive hyperbolic positioning system for
  tracking wildlife using off-the-shelf hardware. Master's dissertation,
  North-West University, Potchefstroom Campus.

Modifications in Thrifty-X:
  - Extended hardware support to Airspy Mini and Airspy R2
    (RTL-SDR remains supported)
  - Migrated codebase from Python 2 to Python 3.10+
  - Added Hardware Abstraction Layer (HAL) for SDR devices
  - Extended I/Q sample processing from 8-bit to 8/12-bit
  - Added configuration validation for Airspy hardware
  - Replaced GnuRadio/osmosdr visualization with matplotlib
  - Added type hints, dataclasses, and modern Python idioms
  - Replaced fastcard C library with fastcapture (libairspy-based)

